nano ~/.ssh/known_hosts
## Press Control-W to enter search mode in nano.
## Now press Control-T to switch to the "jump to line" mode.
## Type the number of the line with the problem key (12 in the example above), Press Return/Enter.
## Now you will be at the beginning of the line with the problem key. Press Control-K to delete this line.
## To exit and save this change, press Control-X. You will be asked if you want to save the modified buffer. Press Y to start the save process. Then press Return/Enter when File Name to Write: is displayed.
